<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="672" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3331/479: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-16T18:00:00-03:00">July 16,
                                    1942—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 16—5:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>595. Guani and I have arranged tentatively to sign the trade agreement on
                            Tuesday, July 21. I shall undoubtedly be asked to make some statement
                            for the press and should appreciate receiving by Sunday any instructions
                            or suggestions which the Department may wish to send me.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>